      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/about/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I’m passionate about understanding how systems are built and how they can be broken. I explore application architecture, build tools to observe real behavior, and write secure code that holds up in production. Instead of relying on surface fixes, I focus on engineering software that’s strong from the inside out.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-i-do&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;#what-i-do&#34; class=&#34;md-heading-anchor&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    What I Do&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I specialize in application security engineering with a strong focus on how systems are designed, abused, and secured in real environments.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
